text: Acleris alnivora is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Russia, China, Japan and Taiwan. The wingspan is about 22 mm. The larvae feed on Alnus japonica var. rufa and Ulmus propinqua.Check List of the Tribe Tortricini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) in Northeast china, with Two Newly Recorded Species from China ==References== Category:Moths described in 1956 alnivora Category:Moths of Asia Category:Moths of Russia
